---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import LegalShell from "../components/LegalShell.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";

const lastUpdated = "April 26, 2026";
const licenseUrl = "https://github.com/maxprain12/dome/blob/main/LICENSE";
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of use — Dome | Intelligent desktop for knowledge and research"
  description="Terms and conditions for using the Dome open-source desktop application, including the custom license and optional third-party services."
>
  <LegalShell title="Terms of use" eyebrow="— Terms" lastUpdated={lastUpdated}>
    <h2>1. Acceptance of terms</h2>
    <p>
      By downloading, installing, or using Dome (“the Application” or “Dome”),
      you agree to these terms. If you do not agree, do not use the Application.
    </p>

    <h2>2. Description of the service</h2>
    <p>
      Dome is an <strong>open-source desktop application</strong> for knowledge
      management and academic research, as described in the
      <a href="https://github.com/maxprain12/dome" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
        >public repository</a
      >. You organize notes, PDFs, videos, and URLs in projects; the app can
      index, search, and help synthesize that material. You may run
      <strong>local or cloud</strong> AI, depending on your configuration
      (Settings and environment).
    </p>

    <h2>3. License to use the software</h2>
    <p>
      The Dome project is distributed under a
      <strong>custom open-source license</strong> in the
      <a href={licenseUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">LICENSE</a>
      file — it is <strong>not</strong> fairly summarized as a stock
      <abbr title="Massachusetts Institute of Technology">MIT</abbr> or
      <abbr title="GNU General Public License">GPL</abbr> grant alone.
      <strong>Free for personal and educational use.</strong>
      <strong>Commercial use requires written permission</strong> from the
      licensor, unless a separate written agreement or the full license text
      in the repository grants otherwise. Read and comply with the
      <a href={licenseUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">LICENSE</a>
      file before commercial redistribution or use.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Source code, documentation, and release artifacts are distributed under the project license on GitHub</li>
      <li>Attribution and any notice requirements in the LICENSE file apply to copies and derivatives</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Use of third-party services</h2>
    <p>
      Optional integrations may connect to third-party services for AI, import,
      calendar, and other features (for example OpenAI, Anthropic, Google, Ollama,
      or MCP servers you configure). Use of those services is subject to
      <strong>their</strong> terms and privacy policies. API keys and tokens you
      provide are stored on your device as implemented in the app.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Intellectual property</h2>
    <p>
      Content you create in Dome (notes, annotations, your library) remains
      yours. The Dome name, logo, and project branding are subject to the
      repository license and any separate trademark or branding policy the
      maintainers publish.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Disclaimer and limitation of liability</h2>
    <p>
      THE APPLICATION IS PROVIDED “AS IS”, WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS
      OR IMPLIED. TO THE MAXIMUM EXTENT PERMITTED BY APPLICABLE LAW, THE AUTHORS
      AND COPYRIGHT HOLDERS ARE NOT LIABLE FOR ANY INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL,
      SPECIAL, CONSEQUENTIAL, OR PUNITIVE DAMAGES, OR ANY LOSS OF DATA OR
      PROFITS, ARISING FROM USE OF OR INABILITY TO USE THE APPLICATION. SEE THE
      LICENSE AND APPLICABLE LAW FOR THE FULL SCOPE.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Contributions</h2>
    <p>
      If you contribute to the project, you agree that your contributions are
      licensed under the same terms the project uses for contributions (as stated
      in the repository’s contributing guidelines and license), and that
      maintainers may need your confirmation for licensing clarity.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Changes to these terms</h2>
    <p>
      These terms may be updated from time to time. The “Last updated” date above
      will change when we publish revisions. Continued use after changes
      constitutes acceptance of the updated terms where permitted by law.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions: <a href="mailto:alder.velasquezobando@gmail.com"
        >alder.velasquezobando@gmail.com</a
      >
      or
      <a
        href="https://github.com/maxprain12/dome"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        >GitHub (issues)</a
      >.
    </p>
  </LegalShell>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
